<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,356,1103]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,356,382]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Length 8.5–9.0 mm. Postocular plate with golden pollinosity. Ocellar bristles well developed. Thorax and abdomen with golden pollinosity. Three well-differentiated post-sutural dorsocentral bristles posteriorly and 1 smaller bristles anteriorly. Apical scutellar bristles present. Legs brownish. T3 with 2 pairs of lateral marginal bristles, T4 with 2 pairs of median marginal and 3 pairs of lateral marginal bristles. ST5 with deep median cleft with margins almost parallel and with pilosity. Cercus straight in lateral view, with expanded obliquely cut apex and dorsal subapical barb. Cercus with bristles ventrally over full length. Cerci with distal third narrower than middle part in posterior view; parallel. Pregonite of equal width from base to apex; unicolorous. Postgonite with expanded base and sudden narrowing at apex; unicolorous. Distiphallus with membranous, smooth ventroapical margin, conical apex, sinuous dorsal outline and notable lateroapical dilation. Vesica symmetrical, with rounded median projection of main branch; distal lobes reduced, with filaments, tapering, partially membranous, with microscopic spines only on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,356,1103]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,753,779]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Remarks.</emphasis>
The cercus and, to some extent, the apical concavity of the distiphallus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge Det. H. S. Lopes" authorityYear="1968" box="[1165,1273,753,779]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamesi">
<emphasis box="[1165,1273,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. jamesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1289,1386,752,779]" captionStart="FIGURES 157–165" captionStartId="68.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[189,1405,303,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-46@68.[151,1435,273,1785]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURES 157–165. Oxysarcodexia spp., males. 157–159. Oxysarcodexia jamesi Dodge (Costa Rica, Guanacaste Province, MNRJ). 157. Habitus, lateral view. 158. Terminalia, lateral view. 159. Terminalia, posterior view. 160–162. Oxysarcodexia laclaricola Souza &amp; Buenaventura, holotype (Colombia, Antioquia, Caldas, La Clara, CE-TdeA). 160. Habitus, lateral view. 161. Terminalia, lateral view. 162. Terminalia, posterior view. 163–165. Oxysarcodexia liliarum Souza &amp; Buenaventura, holotype (Colombia, Antioquia, Caldas, La Clara, CE-TdeA). 163. Habitus, lateral view. 164. Terminalia, lateral view. 165. Terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405651/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 158</figureCitation>
) are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes, 1975 c" authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" box="[364,671,788,815]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[364,511,788,815]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. peculiaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S." box="[519,671,788,815]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="461 - 483" refId="ref110596" refString="Lopes, H. S. (1975 c) New or little known Oxysarcodexia (Diptera, Sarcophagidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 35 (3), 461 - 483." type="journal article" year="1975">Lopes, 1975c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[687,786,788,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 210–218" captionStartId="86.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,368,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-71@86.[151,1435,342,1851]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 210–218. Oxysarcodexia spp., males. 210–212. Oxysarcodexia parva Lopes (Brazil, São Paulo, Campinas, LIE). 210. Habitus, lateral view.211. Terminalia, lateral view. 212. Terminalia, posterior view.213–215. Oxysarcodexia paulistanensis (Mattos) (Brazil, São Paulo, Campinas, LIE). 213. Habitus, lateral view. 214. Terminalia, lateral view. 215. Terminalia, posterior view. 216–218. Oxysarcodexia peculiaris Lopes, holotype (Brazil, Espírito Santo, Linhares, MNRJ). 216. Habitus, lateral view. 217. Terminalia, lateral view. 218. Terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405669/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 217</figureCitation>
). However, the vesica in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge Det. H. S. Lopes" authorityYear="1968" box="[1072,1180,789,815]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamesi">
<emphasis box="[1072,1180,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. jamesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents slender distal lobes, reduced in comparison to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" box="[628,777,824,851]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[628,777,824,851]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and microscopic spines only on ventral surface of distal lobes. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" box="[262,412,860,887]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[262,412,860,887]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the distal lobes of the vesica are expanded and oblong (anterior and lateral views) and covered with small spines on the ventral surface. Female unknown. See also remarks under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1946" box="[1179,1302,897,923]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Oxysarcodexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augusta">
<emphasis box="[1179,1302,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">O. augusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
